Star Africa of Zimbabwe to Sell $22 Million of Assets, CEO Sithole Says

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-08-05T15:07:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/star-africa-of-zimbabwe-to-sell-22-million-of-assets-ceo-sithole-says.html
Star Africa Corp. plans to sell four
units to raise $22 million, its Chief Executive Officer,
Pattison Sithole, said at the company’s annual general meeting
today.  The Harare, Zimbabwe-based company plans to sell Westbev,
Marathon Tyres, Arthur Gardens Engineering and Red Star
Wholesalers, he said.  “The group will continue with its restructuring to remain
with core business which is sugar refining, packaging and
logistics,” Sithole said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  